
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    `github` yek platforme online baraye negahdari va hamkari dar projhe-haye code-nevisi ast. Shoma mitoonid code-haye khod ra upload konid, taghirat ra nyz moratab konid va ba digaran hamkari konid. 

⚙️ **Gozine-ha (related commands):**
    🔹 `git clone <URL>` --> ⬇️ Download kardane yek repository az github be computer shoma.
    🔹 `git push` --> ⬆️ Upload kardane taghirat az computer shoma be github.
    🔹 `git pull` --> 🔄 Gereftane akharin taghirat az github be computer shoma.
    🔹 `git branch` --> 🌿 Sakhtane branch jadid.
    🔹 `git merge` --> 🤝 Yeki kardane taghirat az branch haye mokhtalef.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ git clone https://github.com/username/repositoryname.git

    🔹 Download kardane code az yek repository khass.

    $ git push origin main

    🔹 Upload kardane taghirat az branch `main` be repository github.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ git pull origin main

    🔹 Gereftane akharin taghirat az branch `main` va update kardane local repository.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    `github` is an online platform for storing and collaborating on coding projects. You can upload your code, track changes, and collaborate with others. It's not a command itself, but rather a website/service that works with Git. These examples focus on `git`, the command line tool that interacts with GitHub.

⚙️ **Options (related commands):**
    🔹 `git clone <URL>` --> ⬇️ Download a repository from GitHub to your computer.
    🔹 `git push` --> ⬆️ Upload changes from your computer to GitHub.
    🔹 `git pull` --> 🔄 Fetch the latest changes from GitHub to your computer.
    🔹 `git branch` --> 🌿 Create a new branch.
    🔹 `git merge` --> 🤝 Combine changes from different branches.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ git clone https://github.com/username/repositoryname.git

    🔹 Download code from a specific repository.

    $ git push origin main

    🔹 Upload changes from the `main` branch to the GitHub repository.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ git pull origin main

    🔹 Fetch the latest changes from the `main` branch and update the local repository.
